main event: A white light the size of a star with a red light beneath it was observed over Camp Gagetown, New Brunswick, Canada.
interesting points: The object was observed by ground-radar and visually.
The object moved from east to west at a medium speed of 500 knots.
No further details or analysis were provided in the report.
The observation was reported by the Davis Report and the Department of Transport radio in Fredericton, New Brunswick.
The report was deemed insufficient for a full analysis.
sighted object: a white light the size of a star with a red light beneath it
